description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF together with governmental, civil society and private sector partners continued stimulating behaviour change on key issues reaching over 70% of population. The CO was leading Demand Generation for vaccination and RCCE on COVID-19 to support the national response to pandemic. Complex behaviour change interventions were implemented in WASH, Protection, Health, Education applying such strategies as edutainment, risk awareness, capacity building, community and digital engagement, partnerships and innovations. C4D has rapidly embraced a response actions to the Polio Outbreak since September 2021 leading a Communication & Social Mobilisation pillar and supporting the CO coordination for the response. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
